    "type": "spell",
    "data": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You utter a liberating word of power that frees a creature. You suppress one of the following conditions of your choice: @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.yblD8fOR1J8rDwEQ]{Confused}, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.TBSHQspnbcqxsmjL]{Frightened}, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.kWc1fhmv9LBiTuei]{Grabbed}, or @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.6uEgoh53GbXuHpTF]{Paralyzed}. The target isn't affected by the chosen condition, and if you suppress the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.kWc1fhmv9LBiTuei]{Grabbed} condition, the target automatically breaks free from any grab affecting it when you Cast the Spell.</p>\n<p>If you don't remove the effect that provided the condition, the condition returns after the spell ends. For example, if a spell was making the target @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.yblD8fOR1J8rDwEQ]{Confused} for 1 minute, word of freedom would let the target act normally for a round, but the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.yblD8fOR1J8rDwEQ]{Confused} condition would return afterward.</p>",
